48:49.693 --> 48:53.964 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Finally, a
"NewsHour" Essay.

48:53.998 --> 49:00.671 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Biologist Sheila Patek has faced
criticism
for her research on mantis
shrimp and trap-jaw

49:00.704 --> 49:06.177 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ants. In recent months, members
of Congress
have called her studies a waste
of taxpayer

49:06.210 --> 49:08.012 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
money.

49:08.045 --> 49:12.917 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tonight, she explains how
dismissing her work
misses the aim of scientific
research and

49:12.950 --> 49:14.685 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
discovery.

49:14.718 --> 49:17.488 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHEILA PATEK, Biologist: Some
years ago, I
presented my lab's discoveries
to a group

49:17.521 --> 49:20.257 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of leading thinkers and public
figures.

49:20.291 --> 49:24.829 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We discovered that mantis shrimp
use hammers
equivalent to the mass of two
toothpicks and

49:24.862 --> 49:30.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
move them with the acceleration
of a bullet
to pulverize thick snail shells.
We discovered

49:30.100 --> 49:35.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that tiny trap-jaw ants close
their jaws with
100,000 times the acceleration
of a sprinting

49:35.573 --> 49:37.308 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
cheetah.

49:37.341 --> 49:41.245 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I expressed the wonder of these
discoveries,
as well as their fundamental
significance

49:41.278 --> 49:45.883 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to physics, evolution, and the
limits of current
engineering capabilities.

49:45.916 --> 49:49.987 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A prominent lawyer from Nigeria
who was in
the audience that day approached
me a few

49:50.020 --> 49:57.895 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
