weapons to
resolve conflicts without
killing each other.

51:07.998 --> 51:13.070 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But if you think about it, this
is a fundamental
question for any animal or human
system that

51:13.103 --> 51:18.309 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
has lethal capabilities. In
response to the
Wastebook attack, I was invited
to present

51:18.342 --> 51:20.744 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
my research on Capitol Hill.

51:20.778 --> 51:26.083 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Senator Flake came to the event,
and I spoke
to him one on one. I told him
the story of

51:26.116 --> 51:32.323 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
one of the many unanticipated
paths from my
lab's discoveries to human
applications. I

51:32.356 --> 51:37.094 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
explained how the
extraordinarily intense
impacts of mantis shrimp hammers
inspired

51:37.127 --> 51:39.029 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
engineers to make new materials.

51:39.063 --> 51:44.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One day, this might result in
lightweight,
impact-resistant sports helmets
and military

51:45.002 --> 51:52.843 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
armor. He actually seemed
engaged. So, I asked
him, "Did any of my research
seem worthwhile?"

51:52.876 --> 51:58.248 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Senator Flake said yes. He was
especially
interested in the novel
engineering products.

51:58.282 --> 52:02.920 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
These fundamental discoveries
and their potential
for translation are why my
research program

52:02.953 --> 52:08.392 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is funded by the Department of
Defense and
the National Science Foundation.
However,

52:08.425 --> 52:12.563 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
engineering-related applications
are not the
primary reason we do this
research.

52:12.596 --> 52:18.902 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The nature of discovery is that
it is impossible
to anticipate what you will
find. That is

52:18.936 --> 52:24.541 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
discovery. Discovery-based
research is most
fruitful when new knowledge is
sought for

52:24.575 --> 52:29.113 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
its own sake.

